<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   The Global Markets group is a premier provider of sales, trading, structuring and advisory services to money managers, hedge funds, pension funds, endowments, financial institutions, governments and corporations around the world. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   Our Global Markets business has a major presence in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa and the Pacific Rim, serving clients in virtually all countries. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   Leveraging our local relationships and broad global capabilities, we provide our clients with ideas and market insights, trading services, analytics and new products across a broad spectrum of asset classes - ranging from interest rate and credit products, foreign exchange, real estate and commodities to cash equities and equity-linked products - all with the goal of enabling our clients to maximize their performance. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
   As an Associate within Global Markets, you will: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities </li>
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally </li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
   In trading desk assignments, associates support traders, analyzing client and market data to help develop and execute trades, while learning the basics of risk management and market making. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   Sales roles combine analytical and relationship-building skills and usually involve significant client contact. Working with a senior coverage officer or team to develop and implement a disciplined approach to the sales process, associates typically prepare market and company research, analyze client business activity and may advance rapidly.
</p>
<p class="bac">
   In structuring and origination positions, associates help design and create new securities that enable issuer and investor clients to achieve their objectives. Quantitative skills are indispensable and financial modeling is an important function.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Education</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>MBA or other advanced degree from a top-tier school </li>	
	<li>Superior academic achievement </li>	
	<li>Mathematics, engineering, statistics, or programming background is helpful for some assignments </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Experience</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Minimum of 3 years relevant financial services work experience preferred </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Skills and abilities </H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Strong quantitative and analytical skills </li>	
	<li>Well developed judgment and business sense </li>	
	<li>Demonstrated team, communication, and interpersonal skills </li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Personal traits</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A passionate interest in global financial markets and factors that impact them </li>	
	<li>Extremely motivated with an exceptional internal drive for success </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
   Full-time associates are hired upon completion of their graduate degree. Your career as an associate begins with a formal training program followed by placement in one of our product areas in either a trading, sales, origination or structuring role. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
   The training program takes place in New York for all associates globally, and is considered one of the best in the industry. Instruction is provided by internal professionals and leading business school professors. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The training program includes:
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A firm wide orientation program to introduce you to the bank </li>	
	<li>An overview of the financial markets and essential business skills </li>	
	<li>An intensive training program customized for associates that prepares you for your placement in Global Markets by simulating actual work assignments, covering quantitative fundamentals, and preparing you for life as an associate </li>
</ul>

